Test Cases:

1. Login-

  1st Test Case:
    1. The user will try to type in a new username: Bob1234 
    2. The user will click on the login button. 
    
    Expected Result: [The user will be shown a prompt that they have created a new user.]
    First Result: [No prompt was shown.] - Will continue to work on this functionality.
    Second Result: [There is a console log that the user has created a new user. The homepage changes to indicate they have signed in.] - Success

2nd Test Case:
    1. The user will try to type in the username: Bob1234 
    2. The user will click the login button.
    3. The user will then try to click on the practice words button.
    
    Expected Result: [The user will be shown a prompt that they have logged in. Then, when they click on the practice words button, they will be able to access the practice words page]
    First Result: [No prompt was shown, but they were able to access the practice word page.] - Will continue to work on this functionality.
    Second Result: [There was no prompt shown. The user was is unable to access the practice word page and the add favorite page.] - Success

3rd Test Case:
  1. The user will click the Login button on the homepage.

  Expected Result: [The pop up for logging in with a username will be shown to the user.]
  First Result: [The pop up for logging in does appear on the homepage.] - Success

4th Test Case: 
  1. The user will login to the app
  2. The user will logout to the app

  Expected Result: [The logout button's text will change, so that the text will showcase login]
  First Result: [The logout button's text changed to "login"] - Success

2. Button Functionality -

  1st Test Case:
    1. The user will try to click the practice words button without logging in.
    
    Expected Result: [The user will be unable to go to the practice words page due to not being logged in. A prompt is shown that the user needs to be logged in.]
    First Result: [No prompt was shown, and they were able to access the practice words page.] - Will continue to work on this functionality.

  2nd Test Case:
    1. The user will click the login button without inserting a username

    Expected Result: [The user will be prompted that they need to insert a username depending on which field is missing.]
    First Result: [The user was able to be signed in without entering the field.]
  
  3rd Test Case: 
    1. The user will click the random word button.

    Expected Result: [The user will get a new word generated by the API on the homepage.]
    First Result: [The word Api does generate a new word. The definition sometimes changes.]

  4th Test Case: 
    1. The user will click add to practice while being logged in.

    Expected Result: [The word will appear on the practice page along with the definition if there is a definition]
    First Result: [The word appears on the practice page. The word and definition then changes on the homepage.] - Success

  5th Test Case:
    1. The user will click the button "Add to Favorite"

    Expected Result: [The word will appear in the add to favorites page. Then the word of the day will cycle to a new word and definition on the homepage.]
    First Result: [The word appeared in the add to favorites page.] - Success

2. Page Functionality

    1st Test Case:
      1. The user will click the Practice button on the bottom of the homepage

      Expected Result: [The user will be taken to the practice homepage which gives the recycler view for words]
      First Result: [The user got taken to the practice homepage.] - Success

    2nd Test Case:
      1. The user will click the Favorite button on the bottom of the homepage

      Expected Result: [The user will be taken to the favorite homepage which gives the recycler view for words]
      First Result: [The user got taken to the favorite homepage.] - Success

